    "client_msg_id": "419833e4-6104-4b89-82ca-ba22255e5772",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "_(A shower thought after yet another morning finding and fixing bugs in my own apps.)_\n\nToday some big companies can make apps with shitty logic, poor reliability and bad UX.\n\nToday some developers can make little apps with shitty logic, poor reliability and bad UX. (Occasionally slightly better UX if they're open to designer input.)\n\nI hope recent AI advances empower designers to build little apps with shitty logic, poor reliability and half-decent UX.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1679072369.039309",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
